This paper is about deep neural networks and their theoretical understanding, which is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the usefulness of dropout, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and the study of complexity (cs.SI), which are also possible sub-categories.
